race.comment: STOLEN (4) resumed form a long break with an eye-catching run, finding the well to finish seventh but only a couple of lengths from the winner. Will strip far fitter for it and the extra trip is a huge plus. Won only other try fresh and drawn for a sift run off the inside stall. HIGHLY INTRIGUED (9) is going well and looks a big danger,. Runner-up latest in tougher grade when beaten just a neck and another drawn to have every chance. KIWIESQUE (5) is a lightly raced mare who has changed yards and returns from a break. Worth noting debut win five runs back was this course and distance and was successful. Fitter for a trial and can run well. SHEER LUNACY (1) is going better than recent form suggests and is right in this on best figures.
